{
  "text": "Differences in the prevalence of S. agalactiae internationally may be attributed to different methods of specimen collection, transport media and isolation methods. In the present study chocolate and blood agar were used exclusively as culture media. Use of selective solid culture media such as the Columbia colistin-nalidixic acid (CNA) agar and enrichment broth (Todd-Hewitt supplemented with gentamicin 8 pg/ml) may have yielded higher isolation rates [CITATION_1] .",
